If an invalid portletkey is specified (or the plugin for the legacy portlet is not installed) the dashboard displays this error in the gadget:
{quote}
Error loading gadget: org.apache.shindig.gadgets.GadgetException: Unable to retrieve gadget xml. HTTP error 404
{quote}

This doesn't help the user in any way.  We should make the LegacyPortletResource return a gadget-spec with a nice error message in it also telling the user which portletkey seems to be invalid.

